MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-12 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following:
1) Developing, maintaining, and updating Naval Aviation Technical Publication in IETMS (S1000D) format, manipulating data from raw source data to published digital technical publications;
2) Communicating both orally and in writing to effectively lead and collaborate with a team of at least 5 technical data managers or more;
3) Conducting research on the availability and funds, materials, and time restrictions to successfully negotiate contracts and project requirements to achieve a mutually desired outcome;
4) Assessing the abilities of the department to meet current, future, and contingency requirements and developing plans and programs to enhance capabilities and performance while maintaining cost as an independent variable;
5) Providing necessary training and technical guidance to prepare individuals to successfully support logistics support programs. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management web site: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.

Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-11 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: (1) The ability to interpret strategies, directives, instructions, and policies from higher authority and develop plans and methodologies to ensure compliance. Studies, surveys, and analyses performed by the analyst are of such breadth and scope to require him/her to assume leadership of project teams. Projects, programs, and policies resulting from the analyst's analyses and studies typically involve developing new approaches and means of accomplishing mandated requirements;
(2) The ability to perform tasks which vary from moderate to very complex, requiring an understanding of qualitative and quantitative analytical methods and investigative techniques and skill in performing research and determining procedures for the collection, analysis and compilation of data;
(3) The ability to perform a range of coordinating and supportive duties and responsibilities in support of the supervisor and senior UWDC managers in order to ensure staff activities are executed in a safe, effective, and efficient manner;
(4) The ability to prepare reports, presentations, and correspondence as well as maintain records of work accomplishments and administrative information in order to coordinate preparation and communication of project related information to other organizations by the supervisor. Ability to represent the supervisor in communicating the purpose and need to obtain resources and support from external organizations as well as obtaining needed information or decisions for major work problems and issues that arise;
(5) Proficiency in the use of Microsoft Excel, Power Point, and Word software applications that allows the analyst to conduct analysis from multiple data sources;
(6) Able to prepare and submit written documents supporting analysis with recommendations for courses of action. Ability to review, analyze, and compile a variety of data in order to produce reports and briefings both internal and external to the command; (7) The ability to work independently, managing and monitoring multiple projects simultaneously. The analyst must be able to effectively communicate and interact successfully with managers and staff personnel both internal and external to the command;
(8) Knowledge of government security requirements for classified data and requirements for the proper marking and protection for classified data. Knowledge of requirements for SIPRNET removable media authorization, tracking, and record keeping;
(9) Skill and tact in both oral and written communications. Ability to take notes at meetings and transcribe meeting minutes and action item reports;
(10) Knowledge and skill in applying analytical and evaluative methods and techniques to issues or studies concerning the efficiency and effectiveness of program operations carried out by UWDC. This level includes knowledge of pertinent laws, regulations, policies and precedents which affect the use of program and related support resources (people, money, or equipment);
(11) Knowledge of a wide range of contracting methods and contract types to plan and carry out pre-award and/or post-award procurement actions required of a Contracting Officer Representative (COR). Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management web site: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.

Details.Education:
Education may be substituted for specialized experience as follows:
A Ph.D. or equivalent doctoral degree;
OR
Three full years of progressively higher level graduate education leading to a Ph.D. or equivalent degree;
OR
An LL.M. degree in a field directly related to the position being filled;
OR
A combination of experience and graduate education as described above that equates to one year of experience.

